 <section xml:id="introduction-deploy-alp">
  <title>Introduction</title>
  <para>
   The &alp; (&alpshort;) is a minimal operating system that runs containerized workloads. You can
   run it on a bare metal host, virtualized, or in a cloud environment.
  </para>
 </section>
 <section xml:id="requirements-deploy-alp">
  <title>Requirements</title>
  <itemizedlist>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     Access to the host system - either a bare metal host with supported CPU architecture, or a
     supported hypervisor, or a supported cloud environment.
    </para>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     Internet access to a server with downloadable &alpshort; images.
    </para>
   </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <section xml:id="requirements-supported-architectures">
   <title>Supported architectures</title>
   <para>
    The following CPU architectures are supported:
   </para>
   <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      &x86-64;
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      &arm64;
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </itemizedlist>
  </section>
  <section xml:id="requirements-supported-hypervisors">
   <title>Supported hypervisors</title>
   <para>
    The following virtualization hypervisors are supported:
   </para>
   <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      &kvm;
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      &xen;
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      &vmware;
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      &vbox;
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </itemizedlist>
  </section>
  <section xml:id="requirements-supported-clouds">
   <title>Supported cloud environment</title>
   <para>
    The following cloud environments are supported:
   </para>
   <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      Amazon Web Services (AWS)
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      Microsoft Azure
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </itemizedlist>
  </section>
 </section>
